### PHASE 1: Foundation — Microservices Demo + Jaeger
## Create Project Structure & Clone
# Create project root
mkdir C:\fsbs-demo
cd C:\fsbs-demo

# Clone the Google microservices demo
git clone https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/microservices-demo.git

## Create our working directory for FSBS additions
mkdir fsbs-platform
cd fsbs-platform
mkdir otel-config

Your directory structure:
C:\fsbs-demo\
├── microservices-demo\          ← cloned repo
│   ├── docker-compose.yaml      ← the demo's compose file
│   ├── src\                     ← source code (we won't modify this)
│   └── ...
└── fsbs-platform\               ← our FSBS additions
    └── otel-config\             ← OTel Collector config

## Create the OTel Collector
# Create file C:\fsbs-demo\fsbs-platform\otel-config\otel-collector-config.yaml

## Create the Complete Docker Compose File
# Create file C:\fsbs-demo\fsbs-platform\docker-compose.yaml

## Launch the Stack
cd C:\fsbs-demo\fsbs-platform

# Pull all images first (takes 5-10 minutes on first run)
docker compose pull

# Start everything
docker compose up -d

# Watch the startup logs
docker compose logs -f

# Wait about 60–90 seconds for all services to start. You'll see log output from each service. Look for signs of healthy startup.

# Press Ctrl+C to stop following logs (the services keep running in background).

## Verify All Services are Running
docker compose ps

# You should see all containers with status Up or running

# If any service shows Restarting or Exit, check its logs:  
docker compose logs <service-name>
# e.g., docker compose logs cartservice

##  Record Baseline Metrics
# Collects recent 1000 traces collected within last 5 minutes of time period in Jaeger Collector using curl command
(curl "http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=frontend&limit=1000&lookback=5m" -UseBasicParsing -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Content | python -c "import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); d_list=d.get('data') or []; print(f'Traces found: {len(d_list)}')"

# You should see something like this Traces found: 1000

# Get Avg spans per trace, Typical duration of a span
(curl "http://localhost:16686/api/traces?service=frontend&limit=1000&lookback=5m" -UseBasicParsing -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Content | python -c "import sys,json; d=json.load(sys.stdin); traces=d.get('data') or []; count=len(traces); total_spans=sum(len(t['spans']) for t in traces); total_dur=sum(max(s['startTime'] + s['duration'] for s in t['spans']) - min(s['startTime'] for s in t['spans']) for t in traces) if traces else 0; print(f'--- Metrics for {count} Traces ---'); print(f'Avg Spans per Trace: {total_spans/count:.2f}' if count else 'No traces'); print(f'Avg Trace Duration: {total_dur/count/1000:.2f}ms' if count else '')"

